quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  103,1,"By time,<sup foot_note=197812>1</sup>",footnotes:197812:1
  103,2,"Indeed, mankind is in loss,"
  103,3,"Except for those who have believed and done righteous deeds and advised each other to truth and advised each other to patience."
  104,1,"Woe to every scorner and mocker"
  104,2,"Who collects wealth and [continuously] counts it.<sup foot_note=197813>1</sup>",footnotes:197813:1
  104,3,"He thinks that his wealth will make him immortal."
  104,4,"No! He will surely be thrown into the Crusher.<sup foot_note=197814>1</sup>",footnotes:197814:1
  104,5,"And what can make you know what is the Crusher?"
  104,6,"It is the fire of Allāh, [eternally] fueled,"
  104,7,"Which mounts directed at the hearts.<sup foot_note=197815>1</sup>",footnotes:197815:1
  104,8,"Indeed, it [i.e., Hellfire] will be closed down upon them"
  104,9,"In extended columns.<sup foot_note=197816>1</sup>",footnotes:197816:1
  105,1,"Have you not considered, [O Muḥammad], how your Lord dealt with the companions of the elephant?<sup foot_note=197817>1</sup>",footnotes:197817:1
  105,2,"Did He not make their plan into misguidance?<sup foot_note=197818>1</sup>",footnotes:197818:1
  105,3,"And He sent against them birds in flocks,"
  105,4,"Striking them with stones of hard clay,"
  105,5,"And He made them like eaten straw.<sup foot_note=197819>1</sup>",footnotes:197819:1